===Etymology===
From {{etyl|gml}} *{{term||smilen}} or from a Scandinavian source (Danish and Norwegian Nynorsk {{term|smile}}). Compare Latin {{term|miror|lang=la}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A happy face '''expression''' using mouth, but without producing [[voice]].
#: ''She's got a perfect '''smile'''.''
#: ''He has a sinister '''smile'''.''
#: ''She had a '''smile''' on her face.''
#: ''He always puts a '''smile''' on my face.''

